tm_info.name: Take Down
tm_info.description: A reckless full-body charge attack for slamming into the target. This also damages the user a little.

tm_info.name: Charm
tm_info.description: The user gazes at the target rather charmingly, making it less wary. This harshly lowers the target's Attack stat.

tm_info.name: Fake Tears
tm_info.description: The user feigns crying to fluster the target. This harshly lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Agility
tm_info.description: The user relaxes and lightens its body to move faster. This sharply boosts its Speed stat.

tm_info.name: Mud-Slap
tm_info.description: The user hurls mud in the target's face to inflict damage and lower its accuracy.

tm_info.name: Scary Face
tm_info.description: The user frightens the target with a scary face to harshly lower its Speed stat.

tm_info.name: Protect
tm_info.description: This move enables the user to protect itself from all attacks. Its chance of failing rises if it is used in succession.

tm_info.name: Fire Fang
tm_info.description: The user bites with flame-cloaked fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it with a burn.

tm_info.name: Thunder Fang
tm_info.description: The user bites with electrified fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it with paralysis.

tm_info.name: Ice Fang
tm_info.description: The user bites with cold-infused fangs. This may also make the target flinch or leave it frozen.

tm_info.name: Water Pulse
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target with a pulsing blast of water. This may also confuse the target.

tm_info.name: Low Kick
tm_info.description: A powerful low kick that makes the target fall over. The heavier the target, the greater the move's power.

tm_info.name: Acid Spray
tm_info.description: The user attacks by spitting fluid that works to melt the target. This also harshly lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Acrobatics
tm_info.description: The user nimbly strikes the target. This attack does massive damage if the user isn't holding an item.

tm_info.name: Struggle Bug
tm_info.description: The user attacks by struggling against opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Sp. Atk stats.

tm_info.name: Psybeam
tm_info.description: The target is attacked with a peculiar ray. This may also confuse the target.

tm_info.name: Confuse Ray
tm_info.description: The target is exposed to a sinister ray that causes confusion.

tm_info.name: Thief
tm_info.description: The user attacks and steals the target's held item simultaneously. The user can't steal anything if it already holds an item.

tm_info.name: Disarming Voice
tm_info.description: Letting out a charming cry, the user does emotional damage to opposing Pokémon. This attack never misses.

tm_info.name: Trailblaze
tm_info.description: The user attacks suddenly as if leaping out from tall grass. The user's nimble footwork boosts its Speed stat.

tm_info.name: Pounce
tm_info.description: The user attacks by pouncing on the target. This also lowers the target's Speed stat.

tm_info.name: Chilling Water
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target by showering it with water that's so cold it saps the target's power. This also lowers the target's Attack stat.

tm_info.name: Charge Beam
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target with an electric charge. The residual electricity may also boost the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm_info.name: Fire Spin
tm_info.description: The user traps the target inside a fierce vortex of fire that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

tm_info.name: Facade
tm_info.description: This move's power is doubled if the user is poisoned, burned, or paralyzed.

tm_info.name: Poison Tail
tm_info.description: The user hits the target with its tail. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit and may also poison the target.

tm_info.name: Aerial Ace
tm_info.description: The user confounds the target with speed, then slashes. This attack never misses.

tm_info.name: Bulldoze
tm_info.description: The user strikes everything around it by stomping down on the ground. This lowers the Speed stats of those hit.

tm_info.name: Hex
tm_info.description: This relentless attack does massive damage to a target affected by status conditions.

tm_info.name: Snarl
tm_info.description: The user yells as if it's ranting about something, which lowers the Sp. Atk stats of opposing Pokémon.

tm_info.name: Metal Claw
tm_info.description: The target is raked with steel claws. This may also boost the user's Attack stat.

tm_info.name: Swift
tm_info.description: Star-shaped rays are shot at opposing Pokémon. This attack never misses.

tm_info.name: Magical Leaf
tm_info.description: The user scatters curious leaves that chase the target. This attack never misses.

tm_info.name: Icy Wind
tm_info.description: The user attacks with a gust of chilled air. This also lowers opposing Pokémon's Speed stats.

tm_info.name: Mud Shot
tm_info.description: The user attacks by hurling a blob of mud at the target. This also lowers the target's Speed stat.

tm_info.name: Rock Tomb
tm_info.description: The user hurls boulders at the target to inflict damage. This also lowers the target's Speed stat by cutting off its movement.

tm_info.name: Draining Kiss
tm_info.description: The user steals the target's HP with a kiss. The user's HP is restored by over half the damage taken by the target.

tm_info.name: Flame Charge
tm_info.description: Cloaking itself in flame, the user attacks the target. Then, building up momentum, the user boosts its Speed stat.

tm_info.name: Low Sweep
tm_info.description: The user makes a swift attack on the target's legs, which lowers the target's Speed stat.

tm_info.name: Air Cutter
tm_info.description: The user launches razor-like wind to slash opposing Pokémon. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

tm_info.name: Stored Power
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target with stored power. The more the user's stats are boosted, the greater the move's power.

tm_info.name: Night Shade
tm_info.description: The user makes the target see a frightening mirage. It inflicts damage equal to the user's level.

tm_info.name: Fling
tm_info.description: The user flings its held item at the target to attack. This move's power and effects depend on the item.

tm_info.name: Dragon Tail
tm_info.description: The target is knocked away, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

tm_info.name: Venoshock
tm_info.description: The user drenches the target in a special poisonous liquid. This move's power is doubled if the target is poisoned.

tm_info.name: Avalanche
tm_info.description: This move's power is doubled if the target has inflicted damage on the user in the same turn.

tm_info.name: Endure
tm_info.description: The user endures any attack with at least 1 HP. This move's chance of failing rises if used in succession.

tm_info.name: Volt Switch
tm_info.description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

tm_info.name: Sunny Day
tm_info.description: The user intensifies the sun for five turns, powering up Fire-type attacks. The sunlight also lowers the power of Water-type attacks.

tm_info.name: Rain Dance
tm_info.description: The user summons a heavy rain that falls for five turns, powering up Water-type attacks. The rain also lowers the power of Fire-type attacks.

tm_info.name: Sandstorm
tm_info.description: A five-turn sandstorm is summoned to damage all Pokémon except Rock, Ground, and Steel types. The sandstorm also boosts the Sp. Def stats of Rock types.

tm_info.name: Snowscape
tm_info.description: The user summons a snowstorm lasting five turns. This boosts the Defense stats of Ice types.

tm_info.name: Smart Strike
tm_info.description: The user stabs the target with a sharp horn. This attack never misses.

tm_info.name: Psyshock
tm_info.description: The user materializes an odd psychic wave to attack the target. This move deals physical damage.

tm_info.name: Dig
tm_info.description: The user burrows into the ground on the first turn, then attacks on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Bullet Seed
tm_info.description: The user attacks by forcefully shooting seeds at the target. This move hits two to five times in a row.

tm_info.name: False Swipe
tm_info.description: A restrained attack that prevents the target from fainting. The target is left with at least 1 HP.

tm_info.name: Brick Break
tm_info.description: The user attacks with a swift chop. This move can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.

tm_info.name: Zen Headbutt
tm_info.description: The user focuses its willpower to its head and attacks the target. This may also make the target flinch.

tm_info.name: U-turn
tm_info.description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

tm_info.name: Shadow Claw
tm_info.description: The user attacks by slashing the target with a sharp claw made from shadows. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

tm_info.name: Foul Play
tm_info.description: The user turns the target's strength against it. The higher the target's Attack stat, the greater the damage this move inflicts.

tm_info.name: Psychic Fangs
tm_info.description: The user attacks by biting the target with its psychic capabilities. This move can also break barriers, such as Light Screen and Reflect.

tm_info.name: Bulk Up
tm_info.description: The user tenses its muscles to bulk up its body, boosting its Attack and Defense stats.

tm_info.name: Air Slash
tm_info.description: The user attacks with a blade of air that slices even the sky. This may also make the target flinch.

tm_info.name: Body Slam
tm_info.description: The user attacks by dropping onto the target with its full body weight. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm_info.name: Fire Punch
tm_info.description: The target is attacked with a fiery punch. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm_info.name: Thunder Punch
tm_info.description: The target is attacked with an electrified punch. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm_info.name: Ice Punch
tm_info.description: The target is attacked with an icy punch. This may also leave the target frozen.

tm_info.name: Sleep Talk
tm_info.description: The user randomly uses one of the moves it knows. This move can only be used while the user is asleep.

tm_info.name: Seed Bomb
tm_info.description: The user attacks by slamming a barrage of hard-shelled seeds down on the target from above.

tm_info.name: Electro Ball
tm_info.description: The user hurls an electric orb at the target. The faster the user is than the target, the greater the move's power.

tm_info.name: Drain Punch
tm_info.description: The user attacks with an energy-draining punch. The user's HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

tm_info.name: Reflect
tm_info.description: A wondrous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from physical moves for five turns.

tm_info.name: Light Screen
tm_info.description: A wondrous wall of light is put up to reduce damage from special moves for five turns.

tm_info.name: Rock Blast
tm_info.description: The user attacks by hurling hard rocks at the target. This move hits two to five times in a row.

tm_info.name: Waterfall
tm_info.description: The user charges at the target and may make it flinch.

tm_info.name: Dragon Claw
tm_info.description: The user slashes the target with huge, sharp claws to inflict damage.

tm_info.name: Dazzling Gleam
tm_info.description: The user damages opposing Pokémon by emitting a powerful flash.

tm_info.name: Metronome
tm_info.description: The user waggles a finger and stimulates its brain into randomly using nearly any move.

tm_info.name: Grass Knot
tm_info.description: The user snares the target with grass and trips it. The heavier the target, the greater the move's power.

tm_info.name: Thunder Wave
tm_info.description: The user launches a weak jolt of electricity that paralyzes the target.

tm_info.name: Poison Jab
tm_info.description: The target is stabbed with a tentacle, an arm, or the like steeped in poison. This may also poison the target.

tm_info.name: Stomping Tantrum
tm_info.description: Driven by frustration, the user attacks the target. This move's power is doubled if the user's previous move failed.

tm_info.name: Rest
tm_info.description: The user goes to sleep for two turns. This fully restores the user's HP and cures any status conditions.

tm_info.name: Rock Slide
tm_info.description: Large boulders are hurled at opposing Pokémon to inflict damage. This may also make the opposing Pokémon flinch.

tm_info.name: Taunt
tm_info.description: The target is taunted into a rage that allows it to use only attack moves for three turns.

tm_info.name: Swords Dance
tm_info.description: A frenetic dance to uplift the fighting spirit. This sharply boosts the user's Attack stat.

tm_info.name: Body Press
tm_info.description: The user attacks by slamming its body into the target. The higher the user's Defense stat, the greater the damage this move deals.

tm_info.name: Spikes
tm_info.description: The user lays a trap of spikes at the feet of the opposing team. The spikes will damage opposing Pokémon that switch into battle.

tm_info.name: Toxic Spikes
tm_info.description: The user lays a trap of poison spikes at the feet of the opposing team. The spikes will poison opposing Pokémon that switch into battle.

tm_info.name: Imprison
tm_info.description: If opposing Pokémon know any move also known by the user, they are prevented from using it.

tm_info.name: Flash Cannon
tm_info.description: The user gathers all its light energy and releases it at once. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Dark Pulse
tm_info.description: The user releases a horrible aura imbued with ill intent. This may also make the target flinch.

tm_info.name: Leech Life
tm_info.description: The user drains the target's blood. The user's HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

tm_info.name: Eerie Impulse
tm_info.description: The user's body generates an eerie impulse. Exposing the target to it harshly lowers the target's Sp. Atk stat.

tm_info.name: Fly
tm_info.description: The user flies up into the sky on the first turn, then attacks on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Skill Swap
tm_info.description: The user employs its psychic power to exchange Abilities with the target.

tm_info.name: Iron Head
tm_info.description: The user slams the target with its steel-hard head. This may also make the target flinch.

tm_info.name: Dragon Dance
tm_info.description: The user vigorously performs a mystic, powerful dance that boosts its Attack and Speed stats.

tm_info.name: Power Gem
tm_info.description: The user attacks with a ray of light that sparkles as if it were made of gemstones.

tm_info.name: Gunk Shot
tm_info.description: The user shoots filthy garbage at the target to attack. This may also poison the target.

tm_info.name: Substitute
tm_info.description: The user creates a substitute for itself using some of its own HP. The substitute serves as the user's decoy.

tm_info.name: Iron Defense
tm_info.description: The user hardens its body's surface like iron, sharply boosting its Defense stat.

tm_info.name: X-Scissor
tm_info.description: The user slashes at the target by crossing its scythes, claws, or the like as if they were a pair of scissors.

tm_info.name: Drill Run
tm_info.description: The user crashes into the target while rotating its body like a drill. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

tm_info.name: Will-O-Wisp
tm_info.description: The user shoots a sinister flame at the target to inflict a burn.

tm_info.name: Crunch
tm_info.description: The user crunches up the target with sharp fangs. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

tm_info.name: Trick
tm_info.description: The user catches the target off guard and swaps the target's held item with its own.

tm_info.name: Liquidation
tm_info.description: The user slams into the target using a full-force blast of water. This may also lower the target's Defense stat.

tm_info.name: Giga Drain
tm_info.description: A nutrient-draining attack. The user's HP is restored by up to half the damage taken by the target.

tm_info.name: Aura Sphere
tm_info.description: The user lets loose a pulse of aura power from deep within its body at the target. This attack never misses.

tm_info.name: Tailwind
tm_info.description: The user whips up a turbulent whirlwind that boosts the Speed stats of itself and its allies for four turns.

tm_info.name: Shadow Ball
tm_info.description: The user attacks by hurling a shadowy blob at the target. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Dragon Pulse
tm_info.description: The target is attacked with a shock wave generated by the user's gaping mouth.

tm_info.name: Stealth Rock
tm_info.description: The user lays a trap of levitating stones around the opposing team. The trap damages opposing Pokémon that switch into battle.

tm_info.name: Hyper Voice
tm_info.description: The user attacks by letting loose a horribly loud, resounding cry.

tm_info.name: Heat Wave
tm_info.description: The user attacks by exhaling hot breath on opposing Pokémon. This may also leave them with a burn.

tm_info.name: Energy Ball
tm_info.description: The user draws power from nature and fires it at the target. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Psychic
tm_info.description: The target is hit with a strong telekinetic force to inflict damage. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Heavy Slam
tm_info.description: The user slams into the target with its heavy body. The more the user outweighs the target, the greater the move's power.

tm_info.name: Encore
tm_info.description: The user compels the target to keep using the move it encored for three turns.

tm_info.name: Surf
tm_info.description: The user attacks everything around it by swamping its surroundings with a giant wave.

tm_info.name: Ice Spinner
tm_info.description: The user covers its feet in thin ice and twirls around, slamming into the target. This move's spinning motion also destroys the terrain.

tm_info.name: Flamethrower
tm_info.description: The target is scorched with an intense blast of fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm_info.name: Thunderbolt
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target with a strong electric blast. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm_info.name: Play Rough
tm_info.description: The user attacks by playing rough with the target. This may also lower the target's Attack stat.

tm_info.name: Amnesia
tm_info.description: The user temporarily empties its mind to forget its concerns. This sharply boosts the user's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Calm Mind
tm_info.description: The user quietly focuses its mind and calms its spirit to boost its Sp. Atk and Sp. Def stats.

tm_info.name: Helping Hand
tm_info.description: The user assists an ally by boosting the power of that ally's attack.

tm_info.name: Pollen Puff
tm_info.description: The user attacks the enemy with a pollen puff that explodes. If the target is an ally, it gives the ally a pollen puff that restores its HP instead.

tm_info.name: Baton Pass
tm_info.description: The user switches places with a party Pokémon in waiting and passes along any stat changes.

tm_info.name: Earth Power
tm_info.description: The user makes the ground under the target erupt with power. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Reversal
tm_info.description: An all-out attack that becomes more powerful the less HP the user has.

tm_info.name: Ice Beam
tm_info.description: The target is struck with an icy-cold beam of energy. This may also leave the target frozen.

tm_info.name: Electric Terrain
tm_info.description: The user turns the ground into Electric Terrain for five turns, powering up Electric-type moves. Pokémon on the ground can no longer fall asleep.

tm_info.name: Grassy Terrain
tm_info.description: The user turns the ground into Grassy Terrain for five turns. This restores the HP of Pokémon on the ground a little every turn and powers up Grass-type moves.

tm_info.name: Psychic Terrain
tm_info.description: This protects Pokémon on the ground from priority moves and powers up Psychic-type moves for five turns.

tm_info.name: Misty Terrain
tm_info.description: This protects Pokémon on the ground from status conditions and halves damage from Dragon-type moves for five turns.

tm_info.name: Nasty Plot
tm_info.description: The user stimulates its brain by thinking bad thoughts. This sharply boosts the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm_info.name: Fire Blast
tm_info.description: The target is attacked with an intense blast of all- consuming fire. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm_info.name: Hydro Pump
tm_info.description: The target is blasted by a huge volume of water launched under great pressure.

tm_info.name: Blizzard
tm_info.description: A howling blizzard is summoned to strike opposing Pokémon. This may also leave the opposing Pokémon frozen.

tm_info.name: Fire Pledge
tm_info.description: A column of fire hits the target. When used with its grass counterpart, this move's power is boosted and a vast sea of fire appears.

tm_info.name: Water Pledge
tm_info.description: A column of water hits the target. When used with its fire counterpart, this move's power is boosted and a rainbow appears.

tm_info.name: Grass Pledge
tm_info.description: A column of grass hits the target. When used with its water counterpart, this move's power is boosted and a vast swamp appears.

tm_info.name: Wild Charge
tm_info.description: The user shrouds itself in electricity and smashes into the target. This also damages the user a little.

tm_info.name: Sludge Bomb
tm_info.description: The user hurls unsanitary sludge at the target to inflict damage. This may also poison the target.

tm_info.name: Earthquake
tm_info.description: The user sets off an earthquake that strikes every Pokémon around it.

tm_info.name: Stone Edge
tm_info.description: The user stabs the target with sharpened stones. This move has a heightened chance of landing a critical hit.

tm_info.name: Phantom Force
tm_info.description: The user vanishes somewhere, then strikes the target on the next turn. This move hits even if the target protects itself.

tm_info.name: Giga Impact
tm_info.description: The user charges at the target using every bit of its power. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Blast Burn
tm_info.description: The target is razed by a fiery explosion. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Hydro Cannon
tm_info.description: The target is hit with a watery blast. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Frenzy Plant
tm_info.description: The user slams the target with the roots of an enormous tree. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Outrage
tm_info.description: The user rampages and attacks for two to three turns. The user then becomes confused.

tm_info.name: Overheat
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target with all its might. The recoil from this move harshly lowers the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm_info.name: Focus Blast
tm_info.description: The user heightens its mental focus and unleashes its power. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Leaf Storm
tm_info.description: The user whips up a storm of leaves around the target. The recoil from this move harshly lowers the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm_info.name: Hurricane
tm_info.description: The user attacks by wrapping the target in a fierce wind. This may also confuse the target.

tm_info.name: Trick Room
tm_info.description: The user creates a bizarre area in which slower Pokémon get to move first for five turns.

tm_info.name: Bug Buzz
tm_info.description: The user vibrates to generate a damaging sound wave. This may also lower the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Hyper Beam
tm_info.description: The target is attacked with a powerful beam. The user can't move on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Brave Bird
tm_info.description: The user tucks in its wings and charges at a low altitude. This also damages the user quite a lot.

tm_info.name: Flare Blitz
tm_info.description: The user cloaks itself in fire and charges the target to inflict damage. This also damages the user quite a lot and may leave the target with a burn.

tm_info.name: Thunder
tm_info.description: A wicked thunderbolt is dropped on the target to inflict damage. This may also leave the target with paralysis.

tm_info.name: Close Combat
tm_info.description: The user fights the target up close, inflicting damage without guarding itself. This also lowers the user's Defense and Sp. Def stats.

tm_info.name: Solar Beam
tm_info.description: The user gathers light on the first turn, then blasts a bundled beam on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Draco Meteor
tm_info.description: Comets are summoned down from the sky onto the target. The recoil from this move harshly lowers the user's Sp. Atk stat.

tm_info.name: Steel Beam
tm_info.description: The user fires a beam of steel that it collected from its entire body. This also damages the user.

tm_info.name: Tera Blast
tm_info.description: If the user has Terastallized, it unleashes energy of its Tera Type. This move inflicts damage using the Attack or Sp. Atk stat-whichever is higher for the user.Stellar: Inflicts damage with the user's Attack or Sp. Atk stat- whichever is higher. Super effective against Terastallized targets. This lowers the user's Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

tm_info.name: Roar
tm_info.description: The target is scared off, and a different Pokémon is dragged out. In the wild, this ends a battle against a single Pokémon.

tm_info.name: Charge
tm_info.description: The user becomes charged, boosting the power of the next Electric-type move it uses. This also boosts the user's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Haze
tm_info.description: The user creates a haze that eliminates every stat change among all the Pokémon engaged in battle.

tm_info.name: Toxic
tm_info.description: A move that leaves the target badly poisoned. Its poison damage worsens every turn.

tm_info.name: Sand Tomb
tm_info.description: The user traps the target inside a harshly raging sandstorm that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

tm_info.name: Spite
tm_info.description: The user unleashes its grudge on the move last used by the target by cutting 4 PP from it.

tm_info.name: Gravity
tm_info.description: Enables Flying types or Pokémon with the Levitate Ability to be hit by Ground-type moves for five turns. Moves that involve flying can't be used.

tm_info.name: Smack Down
tm_info.description: The user throws a stone or similar projectile to attack the target. If the target is in the air, it will be knocked down to the ground.

tm_info.name: Gyro Ball
tm_info.description: The user tackles the target with a high-speed spin. The slower the user is than the target, the greater the move's power.

tm_info.name: Knock Off
tm_info.description: The user slaps down the target's held item, making it unusable for that battle. This move does more damage if the target has a held item.

tm_info.name: Bug Bite
tm_info.description: The user attacks by biting the target. If the target is holding a Berry, the user eats it and gains its effect.

tm_info.name: Super Fang
tm_info.description: The user chomps hard on the target with its sharp front fangs. This cuts the target's HP in half.

tm_info.name: Vacuum Wave
tm_info.description: The user whirls its fists to send a wave of pure vacuum at the target. This move always goes first.

tm_info.name: Lunge
tm_info.description: The user makes a lunge at the target, attacking with full force. This also lowers the target's Attack stat.

tm_info.name: High Horsepower
tm_info.description: The user fiercely attacks the target using its entire body.

tm_info.name: Icicle Spear
tm_info.description: The user attacks by launching sharp icicles at the target. This move hits two to five times in a row.

tm_info.name: Scald
tm_info.description: The user attacks by shooting boiling hot water at the target. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm_info.name: Heat Crash
tm_info.description: The user slams into the target with its flame-covered body. The more the user outweighs the target, the greater the move's power.

tm_info.name: Solar Blade
tm_info.description: The user gathers light on the first turn, then fills a blade with the light's energy and attacks on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Uproar
tm_info.description: The user attacks in an uproar for three turns. During that time, no Pokémon can fall asleep.

tm_info.name: Focus Punch
tm_info.description: The user focuses its mind before launching a punch. This move fails if the user is hit before using the move.

tm_info.name: Weather Ball
tm_info.description: This move's type and power change depending on the weather at the time the move is used.

tm_info.name: Grassy Glide
tm_info.description: Gliding on the ground, the user attacks the target. This move always goes first on Grassy Terrain.

tm_info.name: Burning Jealousy
tm_info.description: The user attacks with energy from jealousy. This leaves all opposing Pokémon that have had their stats boosted during the turn with a burn.

tm_info.name: Flip Turn
tm_info.description: After making its attack, the user rushes back to switch places with a party Pokémon in waiting.

tm_info.name: Dual Wingbeat
tm_info.description: The user slams the target with its wings to inflict damage. The target is hit twice in a row.

tm_info.name: Poltergeist
tm_info.description: The user attacks by controlling the target's item. This move fails if the target isn't holding an item.

tm_info.name: Lash Out
tm_info.description: The user lashes out to vent its frustration toward the target. This move's power is doubled if the user's stats were lowered during this turn.

tm_info.name: Scale Shot
tm_info.description: The user attacks by shooting scales two to five times in a row. This move boosts the user's Speed stat but lowers its Defense stat.

tm_info.name: Misty Explosion
tm_info.description: The user attacks everything around it and faints upon using this move. This move's power is boosted on Misty Terrain.

tm_info.name: Pain Split
tm_info.description: The user adds its HP to the target's HP, then equally splits the combined HP between the target and itself.

tm_info.name: Psych Up
tm_info.description: The user hypnotizes itself into copying any stat change made by the target.

tm_info.name: Double-Edge
tm_info.description: A reckless life-risking tackle in which the user rushes the target. This also damages the user quite a lot.

tm_info.name: Endeavor
tm_info.description: The user inflicts damage by cutting down the target's HP to roughly equal the user's HP.

tm_info.name: Petal Blizzard
tm_info.description: The user stirs up a violent petal blizzard and damages everything around it.

tm_info.name: Temper Flare
tm_info.description: Spurred by desperation, the user attacks the target. This move's power is doubled if the user's previous move failed.

tm_info.name: Whirlpool
tm_info.description: The user traps the target inside a violent, swirling whirlpool that inflicts damage for four to five turns.

tm_info.name: Muddy Water
tm_info.description: The user attacks by shooting muddy water at opposing Pokémon. This may also lower their accuracy.

tm_info.name: Supercell Slam
tm_info.description: The user electrifies its body and drops onto the target to inflict damage. If this move misses, the user takes damage instead.

tm_info.name: Electroweb
tm_info.description: The user captures opposing Pokémon in an electric net to inflict damage. This also lowers their Speed stats.

tm_info.name: Triple Axel
tm_info.description: A consecutive three-kick attack that becomes more powerful with each successful hit.

tm_info.name: Coaching
tm_info.description: The user properly coaches its ally Pokémon, boosting their Attack and Defense stats.

tm_info.name: Sludge Wave
tm_info.description: The user strikes everything around it by swamping the area with a giant sludge wave. This may also poison those it hits.

tm_info.name: Scorching Sands
tm_info.description: The user throws scorching sand at the target to attack. This may also leave the target with a burn.

tm_info.name: Feather Dance
tm_info.description: The user covers the target's body with a mass of down that harshly lowers its Attack stat.

tm_info.name: Future Sight
tm_info.description: Two turns after this move is used, a hunk of psychic energy attacks the target.

tm_info.name: Expanding Force
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target with its psychic power. When the ground is Psychic Terrain, this move's power is boosted and it damages all opposing Pokémon.

tm_info.name: Skitter Smack
tm_info.description: The user skitters behind the target to attack. This also lowers the target's Sp. Atk stat.

tm_info.name: Meteor Beam
tm_info.description: The user gathers energy from space and boosts its Sp. Atk stat on the first turn, then attacks on the next turn.

tm_info.name: Throat Chop
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target's throat, and the resultant suffering prevents the target from using sound-based moves for two turns.

tm_info.name: Breaking Swipe
tm_info.description: The user swings its tough tail wildly and attacks opposing Pokémon. This also lowers their Attack stats.

tm_info.name: Metal Sound
tm_info.description: A horrible sound like scraping metal harshly lowers the target's Sp. Def stat.

tm_info.name: Curse
tm_info.description: A move that has different effects depending on whether the user is a Ghost type or not.

tm_info.name: Hard Press
tm_info.description: The target is crushed with an arm, a claw, or the like to inflict damage. The more HP the target has left, the greater the move's power.

tm_info.name: Dragon Cheer
tm_info.description: The user raises its allies' morale with a draconic cry so that their future attacks have a heightened chance of landing critical hits. This rouses Dragon types more.

tm_info.name: Alluring Voice
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target using its angelic voice. This also confuses the target if its stats have been boosted during the turn.

tm_info.name: Psychic Noise
tm_info.description: The user attacks the target with unpleasant sound waves. For two turns, the target is prevented from recovering HP through moves, Abilities, or held items.

tm_info.name: Upper Hand
tm_info.description: The user reacts to the target's movement and strikes with the heel of its palm, making the target flinch. This move fails if the target is not readying a priority move.
